questions.questionTitle: Lis Room 301 - Part 3 - Topic : Community  - Nam nói trước
questions.content: Topic : Community - Nam nói trước
questions.suggestion:
15. Topic : Community design - BWMB ( 0120 ) - Nam nói trước

- Building design can influence people’s behavior: B

- Creating community can take time: W

- Work communities and social communities are the same: M

- Technology has changed how the community forms: B


Giải thích:

Man: You know, I believe building design can shape people’s behaviors and interactions from the start. When spaces are designed well, people feel comfortable and naturally start connecting.

Giải thích:

Woman: Of course, design matters, but there’s no shortcut to building real community connections. Creating community takes time and consistency, even in spaces that encourage interaction.

Giải thích:

Man: Really? But I also feel that work communities and social communities aren’t as different as we might think. Both require spaces that help people feel connected and valued, whether it’s at work or in social settings.

Giải thích:

Man: Yes, I agree, but I think technology has really changed how communities form. It makes connecting so much easier, and people don’t always need to meet face-to-face to feel a sense of connection.

Woman: I see that, but I don’t think online connections can fully replace in-person gatherings.

questions.suggestion:
15. Topic : Community design - BWMB ( 0120 ) - Nam nói trước

- Building design can influence people’s behavior: B

- Creating community can take time: W

- Work communities and social communities are the same: M

- Technology has changed how the community forms: B


Giải thích:

Man: You know, I believe building design can shape people’s behaviors and interactions from the start. When spaces are designed well, people feel comfortable and naturally start connecting.

Giải thích:

Woman: Of course, design matters, but there’s no shortcut to building real community connections. Creating community takes time and consistency, even in spaces that encourage interaction.

Giải thích:

Man: Really? But I also feel that work communities and social communities aren’t as different as we might think. Both require spaces that help people feel connected and valued, whether it’s at work or in social settings.

Giải thích:

Man: Yes, I agree, but I think technology has really changed how communities form. It makes connecting so much easier, and people don’t always need to meet face-to-face to feel a sense of connection.

Woman: I see that, but I don’t think online connections can fully replace in-person gatherings.

questions.questionTitle: Lis Room 301 - Part 3 - Topic : Community  - Nam nói trước
questions.content: Topic : Community - Nam nói trước
questions.suggestion:
15. Topic : Community design - BWMB ( 0120 ) - Nam nói trước

- Building design can influence people’s behavior: B

- Creating community can take time: W

- Work communities and social communities are the same: M

- Technology has changed how the community forms: B


Giải thích:

Man: You know, I believe building design can shape people’s behaviors and interactions from the start. When spaces are designed well, people feel comfortable and naturally start connecting.

Giải thích:

Woman: Of course, design matters, but there’s no shortcut to building real community connections. Creating community takes time and consistency, even in spaces that encourage interaction.

Giải thích:

Man: Really? But I also feel that work communities and social communities aren’t as different as we might think. Both require spaces that help people feel connected and valued, whether it’s at work or in social settings.

Giải thích:

Man: Yes, I agree, but I think technology has really changed how communities form. It makes connecting so much easier, and people don’t always need to meet face-to-face to feel a sense of connection.

Woman: I see that, but I don’t think online connections can fully replace in-person gatherings.


THIẾT KẾ 01 TÒA NHÀ CÓ THỂ MẤT THỜI GIAN là 20 năm vì chưa có CÔNG NGHỆ
